        "responses": {
          "values": [
            {
              "role": "system",
              "content": "=You are an expense-parsing assistant. Extract structured data from a sentence describing a shared expense written by \"the current user.\"\n\nRULES:\n1. \"I\", \"me\", and \"myself\" always refer to the current user. In the output, the current user must ALWAYS be written as the exact string \"You\" \u2014 never output \"I\", \"me\", or any other pronoun as a literal value anywhere in the JSON.\n2. The PAYER is whoever performed the paying action in the sentence \u2014 identify this by finding who the sentence says \"paid.\" This can be the current user (You) or another named person. Do not default to \"You\" just because \"I\" or \"me\" appears somewhere in the sentence \u2014 read the full sentence structure first.\n3. PARTICIPANTS are everyone splitting the cost, including the payer themselves if they are also splitting it, and including the current user (You) if mentioned as a participant.\n4. AMOUNT must be a plain number, no currency symbols, no extra text.\n5. If you cannot confidently identify a Payer AND an Amount AND at least one Participant from the sentence, do not guess \u2014 return exactly this JSON and nothing else: {\"error\": \"unable to parse\", \"reason\": \"<short explanation>\"}\n\nOUTPUT FORMAT \u2014 return strict JSON only, no explanation, no markdown fences:\n{\"payer\": \"<name or You>\", \"amount\": <number>, \"participants\": [\"<name or You>\", \"...\"]}\n\nEXAMPLES:\n\"I paid 40 for dinner with Alex and Sam\" \u2192 {\"payer\": \"You\", \"amount\": 40, \"participants\": [\"Alex\", \"Sam\"]}\n\"Sam paid 60 for groceries with me and Alex\" \u2192 {\"payer\": \"Sam\", \"amount\": 60, \"participants\": [\"You\", \"Alex\"]}\n\"Alex paid 30 and I was there with Sam\" \u2192 {\"payer\": \"Alex\", \"amount\": 30, \"participants\": [\"You\", \"Sam\"]}\n\"split lunch\" \u2192 {\"error\": \"unable to parse\", \"reason\": \"no amount specified\"}"
            },
            {
              "content": "={{ $json.body.message }}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "builtInTools": {},
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.openAi",
      "typeVersion": 2.3,
